profile_positions.description:
• Individual and team research on lifelong learning, eLearning, open learning-research-education, personalised learning, PLE, adaptivity, intelligent tutoring systems, social semantic web, cloud teamworking,  change management, learning organizations, language learning;
• coordination of the following selected projects:
1. Format QRcode: creator of the format (within the research project Learning4All, 2009-2012, with the Università Politecnica delle Marche), coordinator of all the 9 research experiences (2010-2012) and facilitator/teacher in 7 of them (for 184 learners in all, over 120 hours F2F and 900 hours in the eLearning environments at www.elearningplace.it/corsi) and designer of the eLearning environments used;
2. SSW4LL – Social Semantic Web for Lifelong Learners (from October 2011): author and coordinator of the research experience and facilitator/teacher, for 33 ICT and eLearning professionals, over 4 weeks/400 hours entirely in the eLearning environment (designed ad hoc) in www.elearningplace.it/ssw4ll;
3. PlaLE - Personal language Learning Environment (school years 2011/12, 2012/13 and 2013/14): coordinator of the technological-educational innovation and teacher, for 405 high school students of English as a foreign language (and microlanguage – economy and surveying, over 740 hours F2F and 400 hours in the eLearning environment (that was designed ad hoc) in www.elearningplace.it/corsi;
4. uProf! – Ubiquitous Professional Training for Teachers: co-creator of the model (with Giovanni Biancofiore) and coordinator of its research experiences with Italian high school teachers members of the school network Eureka;
5. Eureka project (2012–2014, a network of 11 middle and high schools): coordinator of the technological-educational innovation and trainer for 80 teachers, F2F and in the eLearning environment Comunità di Pratica Progetto Eureka in www.elearningplace.it/corsi).
• publications and presentations at international conferences and seminars/webinars.

Research on technologies for distance learning (scientific collaboration with the Athabasca University, Canada, the National Sun Yat-sen University, Taiwan, and various research institutes and Italian universities), in particular experiences on:
1.	inclusive learning using ICT (research project FIRB Learning for All, 2009-2012);
2.	integration of paper-based and digital learning material by QR code;
3.	wikis in general and as learning tools;
4.	metadata, standards (SCORM and Common Cartridge) and interoperability;
5.	adaptivity of learning systems and ITS (Intelligent Tutoring Systems) – implementation of the module iLMS in Moodle;
6.	learning in virtual classroom (synchronous cyber classroom, blended synchronous learning model, tests and assessment in synchronous cyber classrooms);
7.	communities of practice, organizational learning and learning organizations;
8.	evaluation, use and integration in Moodle of rapid e-learning prototyping software for the development of multimedia and interactive learning objects;
9.	digital repositories within large networks of education systems and universities;
10.	evaluation of some relational database;
11.	Moodle and Second Life (Sloodle module);
12.	Personal Learning Environments, adaptivity, ITS, Social Semantic Web, lifelong learning, relation between formal and informal learning, users’ profiling in university courses.
Publications and presentations at international conferences and seminars/webinars.

•	Member of the Technical Program Committee and workshops chair of ELEOT 2016 (Aug 31 – Sep 2, Dublin, Ireland);
•	Member of the Technical Program Committee of the 2016 International Workshop on Advanced E-Learning In conjunction with the 9th IEEE U-Media 2016 (Aug 15-16, 2016, Moscow, Russia);
•	Reviewer for ASCILITE 2015 Conference (29 Nov – 2 Dec, Perth, Western Australia);
•	Workshops Chair and Member of the Technical Program Committee of ELEOT 2015 - EAI International Conference on e-Learning, e-Education and Online Training (Sep 16-18, Novedrate, Italy);
•	Examiner of the PhD thesis Dynamic course composition for adaptive e-learning (2014), Faculty of Information and Communication Engineering, Anna University, Chennai, India;
•	Reviewer of chapters of the book Handbook of Research on Electronic Democracy and Government (2015), K. J. Bwalya (ed.), IGI Global. 
•	Reviewer for ASCILITE 2014 Conference (23-26 November, Dunedin, New Zealand);
•	Member of the Technical Program Committee of ELEOT 2014 - EAI International Conference on e-Learning, e-Education and Online Training (Sep 18-20, Bethesda, MD, USA);
•	Reviewer of chapters of the book Encyclopaedia of Information Science and Technology (3rd Edition) (2014), M. Khosrow-Pour (ed.), IGI Global;
•	Reviewer for ASCILITE 2013 Conference (1-4 Dec, Sydney, Australia);
•	Reviewer for ASCILITE 2012 Conference (25-28 Nov, Wellington, New Zealand);
•	Reviewer of chapters of the book Developing and utilizing e-learning applications (2010), F. Lazarinis, S. Green & E. Pearson (eds.), IGI Global;
•	Reviewer for CELDA, IADIS International Conference Cognition and Exploratory Learning in Digital Age (20-22 Nov 2010, Rome, Italy);
•	Reviewer for HERDSA 2009 International Teaching and Learning conference (6-9 July, Charles Darwin University, Darwin, NT, Australia);
•	Reviewer of chapters of the book Technology Supported Environment for Personalised Learning: Methods and Case Studies (2009), J. O'Donoghue (ed.), IGI Global.

•	Design of face-to-face and distance (e-learning) teaching and learning strategies. 
•	Analysis of learning needs and planning of personalised learning solutions. 
•	Planning and management of teaching activities and logistics;
•	Procurement for open learning solutions; 
•	Transfer of know-how and contents about the orientation within the business environment, the development of business ideas, business process analysis and strategic planning, strategic and operative marketing, customer satisfaction, problem solving, Total Quality Management and quality systems, standard and business English and French, technology-enhanced learning.

•	currently on research leave.

Main tasks:
•	Curricular teaching (instructional design methodology) and connected activities (director of multimedia language labs; class coordinator; commissioner of high school final exam);
•	Planning, organization and management of extracurricular paths:
	deepening of contents (in regionally and nationally funded projects);
	interdisciplinary and cooperative learning projects;
	cultural exchange European Union’s projects;
	courses for the preparation for Trinity and Cambridge Exams.
